Confirmatory Analyses File: "Adult Age Differences in Remembering Gain- and Loss-Related Intentions" 

Data from N=180 participants (age range: 18-85 years) who completed an event-based prospective memory task and a battery of cognitive tests and questionnaires in the laboratory. Participants were randomly assigned to one of three experimental groups/conditions: (1) control condition, (2) gain-frame condition, (3) loss-frame condition.

The registered Stage-1 protocol (including hypotheses, methods, and sample size planning) can be found at the Open Science Framework at: https://osf.io/mv4y3

Reference: Protocol registration for the stage-1 manuscript (with in principle acceptance): Horn, S., & Freund, A. M. (2020). [Stage-1 Registered Report, in principle acceptance]: Adult-Age Differences in Remembering Gain- and Loss-Related Intentions. Cognition and Emotion.
